    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices used to cut patterns into leather or other materials, originally parts for the uppers of boots and shoes, but now typically for any material intended for garments. These now are in the form of hand or hydraulic presses fixed with dies.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
